text: Welcome to our lecture on Data Types and Variables in Python. Today, we'll explore the foundational elements of programming in Python: data types and variables.

Understanding these concepts is crucial as they form the building blocks for more complex programming tasks. We'll start with an overview of basic data types such as integers, floats, strings, lists, tuples, dictionaries, and sets.

By the end of this session, you should feel confident in creating and manipulating basic data structures in Python, understand the importance of proper data type selection, and perform arithmetic operations and manipulations using variables.
